            "description": "Two-loop vertex integral N3 entering the Zbb form factor (Fleischer:1998nb, Dubovyk:2016zok), with one massive propagator (mass $m_Z$) and the on-shell condition $s = p_3^2 = m_Z^2$. The kinematics has no Euclidean region: the second Symanzik polynomial $F$ vanishes on a hyperplane in Feynman parameter space, producing endpoint singularities at $x_i=1$ in addition to those at the origin. pySecDec uses a dedicated splitting procedure (avoiding the symmetric point $x_i=0.5$) to remap these into origin singularities. Numerical results through $\\varepsilon^0$ are reported in Tab. N3.",
